ucation.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-2019\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/hr-handshaking-successful-candidate-getting-hired-new-job-closeup.jpg\" alt=\"why study in the usa\" width=\"821\" height=\"548\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/hr-handshaking-successful-candidate-getting-hired-new-job-closeup.jpg 821w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/hr-handshaking-successful-candidate-getting-hired-new-job-closeup-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/11\/hr-handshaking-successful-candidate-getting-hired-new-job-closeup-768x513.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 821px) 100vw, 821px\" \/><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">3. Diverse Career Opportunities<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Choosing an international degree from the US not only expands global exposure but also unlocks a variety of career paths.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Upon returning home, many students find lucrative job opportunities, thanks to the highly esteemed degrees earned from great US universities.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">These institutions actively support internships, providing valuable hands-on experience that boosts employability and opens doors to well-paying jobs.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Look at some statistics about the international degree from the US for career benefits:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Increased Job Opportunities:<\/strong> A <a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.iie.org\/news\/us-hosts-over-1-million-fastest-growth-for-40-years\/\">study by the Institute of International Education (IIE)<\/a> revealed that 68% of international students who graduated from US universities in 2018 secured full-time employment within six months, compared to a 51% employment rate for US graduates.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Higher Salaries:<\/strong> International graduates from US universities tend to earn higher salaries. A <a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.glassdoor.com\/blog\/mission-culture-survey\/\">2019 Glassdoor study<\/a> found that the median salary for international graduates was $63,000, compared to $52,000 for US graduates.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Global Career Advancement:<\/strong> An international degree from the US can open doors to career opportunities in other countries. A <a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.topuniversities.com\/university-rankings\/world-university-rankings\/2019\">2019 QS World University Rankings survey<\/a> showed that 72% of international students from US universities worked in a foreign country in the past five years.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">These are some data regarding internships and hands-on experience:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Internship Participation:<\/strong> According to <a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.iie.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/SpringSnapshot_Final.pdf\">the IIE<\/a>, 96% of international students at US universities participate in internships or other forms of experiential learning.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Impact on Employment:<\/strong> An <a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.naceweb.org\/talent-acquisition\/candidate-selection\/internship-experience-the-top-differentiator-when-choosing-between-otherwise-equal-job-candidates\/\">NACE study<\/a> found that 82% of employers consider internship experience &#8220;very important&#8221; when hiring recent graduates.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Salary Benefits:<\/strong> Internships can lead to higher salaries. A <a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.naceweb.org\/about-us\/advocacy\/position-statements\/6bcb7e07-b277-41a2-bc09-1bca8c2bfd58\">2019 NACE study<\/a> found that interns with relevant experience were offered starting wages 10% higher than those without internship experience.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The overall impact of an international degree from the US and why study in the USA as an international student include:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Economic Contribution:<\/strong> International students contribute billions to the US economy each year. In 2018, they contributed <a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.iie.org\/news\/number-of-international-students-in-the-united-states-hits-all-time-high\/\">an estimated $44.7 billion<\/a>, according to the US Department of Commerce.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Cultural Exchange:<\/strong> International students promote cultural exchange and understanding between the US and other countries.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>Global Leadership:<\/strong> A <a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.iie.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/12\/International-Students-in-the-US.pdf\">study by the IIE<\/a> found that 70% of international students who graduated from US universities in the past five years are now in leadership roles in their home countries.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">4. Flexibility in Education, Why Study in the USA<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">US universities set themselves apart by offering various subjects aligned with students&#8217; diverse interests. Unlike in many home countries, students are not pressured to declare their major in the first year of their bachelor&#8217;s program.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The flexibility to choose a major in the second year allows students the time and space to explore their passions, fostering a deeper understanding of their chosen field for future.<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><a style=\"color: #333333;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.insidehighered.com\/news\/2016\/08\/24\/study-finds-students-benefit-waiting-declare-major\">More than 80% of US universities<\/a> allow students to explore different majors before declaring one, offering the opportunity to take courses in various subjects before deciding on a specific study area. It helps students discover their passions and interests, leading to a more informed decision about their major.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students take 12 courses on average before declaring a major, providing ample time to explore different subjects and establish a solid foundation in their chosen field.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students who declare a major later in their undergraduate career often have higher GPAs than those who claim earlier, likely because they&#8217;ve had more time to explore their interests and find a subject they are passionate about.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Flexibility in exploring different majors increases the likelihood of on-time graduation, as students are less likely to switch majors, which can cause delays.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Graduating with a major is passionate about increases career satisfaction, as individuals are more likely to find a job that aligns with their skills and interests.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">These data and statistics highlight the value of educational flexibility in US universities, enabling students to explore their interests, make informed decisions about their major, and graduate with a degree they are passionate about.<\/span><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"color: #333333;\">5. Optimal Return on Investment<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Students often grapple with mounting study loans and escalating interest rates in an era of rapid educational transformation. Choosing a university based on ROI becomes crucial.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">US universities enhance skill sets and promise better returns post-graduation, making them a strategic choice for those seeking a valuable and enduring investment in their education.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #333333;\">The following are some statistics about the optimal ROI of US universities:<\/span><\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Median ROI of US universities over 40 years:<\/span>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">$918,000 for a bachelor&#8217;s degree from a US university.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">$683,000 for a bachelor&#8217;s degree from a public US university.<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">$1,153,000 for a bachelor&#8217;s degree from a private US university.<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Top 10 US universities with the highest ROI:<\/span>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Princeton University<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Yale University<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Harvard University<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Stanford University<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">University of Pennsylvania<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Columbia University<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">California Institute of Technology (Caltech)<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">University of Chicago<\/span><\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Northwestern University<\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/li>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\">Factors Affecting ROI:<\/span>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"color: #333333;\"><strong>C